{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cf6da182-61dc-4a8f-9594-cdcb18bd9feb","content":"The issue is file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed **before** them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed first but depends on `Domain.fs`. The fix is to reorder them:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_tUF7LN6XH3PUwD4x72Aw2H","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-a16959bf2984432a9e397b8c6bc6fe05/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-a16959bf2984432a9e397b8c6bc6fe05/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"4c107b41-8535-414d-94ea-f21d03cf4342","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first) - opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second) - defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` (listed third) - opens both Domain and Services\n\nThe fix is to reorder the files so `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":433,"requestId":"280E:926CA:1AFD833:1E0E897:69FA8FEA"},"id":"a8524706-fcf7-4fde-95af-a46124067d95","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:48:50.469Z","parentId":"ae7ebd88-1fb8-432e-aac5-3759dc43390a"}
